President Obama has announced the appointment of Ambassador Donald Booth as the new U.S. Special Envoy for Sudan and South Sudan. Ambassador Booth is a highly experienced diplomat with a strong background in promoting peace and preventing conflict in Africa. He will be responsible for implementing agreements between Sudan and South Sudan and resolving outstanding issues, such as borders and the final status of Abyei. Additionally, Ambassador Booth will work towards ending conflicts in Blue Nile, Southern Kordofan, and Darfur, as well as promoting inclusive governance and human rights in both countries. The President expressed confidence in Ambassador Booth's abilities to advance U.S. interests and achieve lasting peace in the region.